snippet: The plane, said to be carrying more than 100 passengers and crew members, went down in rough weather, according to the military.
abstract: Algerian military plane crashes in mountainous area of northeastern Algeria, killing at least 77 of more than 100 passengers and crew members; incident marks first major crash in the country in more than a decade.
lead_paragraph: The plane, said to be carrying more than 100 passengers and crew members, went down in rough weather, according to the military.

headline.main: Military Plane Crash in Algeria Leaves Scores Dead
headline.print_headline: Plane Crash Said to Leave Scores Dead in Algeria
